h3. Issue Summary

Basically, this behavior is  similar to the following report:
 - https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-37267

However, in this case, it doesn't matter if the issue is being created by opening a new tab or not, the behavior will still be the same.
h3. Steps to reproduce this behavior:

1. User opens a dialog window to create an issue;
2. Clicks Create.
3. The user sees the same window activated with the same data and is clicking again Create.
h3. Expected results:

It is possible to create one issue only.
h3. Actual results:

Multiple duplicate issues were created with the same Summary field being created.
h3. Notes:

Differently from previous cases, when you click directly on the create issue button, the create issue form will appear in a popup form, however, the same behavior will still happen.

When analyzing the HAR files, this is what is actually happening, separated by steps:

1. User opens a dialog window to create an issue;
2. Clicks Submit;
3. POST request is being sent to the server;
4. Dialog window and button Create is being deactivated;
5. VPN is disconnecting (from the internal network where JIRA server is held) during the POST request processing;
6. Dialog window and submit button is being activated;
7. POST request still doesn't have an answer;
8. User sees the same window activated with the same data and is clicking again Create;
9. Second POST request is being sent.
h3. Workaround:

No workarounds found so far for this behavior

When associating a custom field to a screen there should be a Select All option instead of having to select all the screens individually.
{panel}
 # Under *Fields*, click *Custom fields*.
 # Find the custom field and click   !https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiracloud/files/945104543/953138835/1/1530293342730/meatballs.png|height=18!  > *Screens*. 
 # There is no *Select All* option to just add the Custom Field to all screens{panel}
This option will be helpful when not using a Default Screen and using custom screens to add the field to all screens.
